org.jetel.data

Class StringDataField

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.data.DataField
      • org.jetel.data.DataFieldImpl
        • org.jetel.data.StringDataField
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Appendable, java.lang.CharSequence, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>

    public class StringDataField
extends DataFieldImpl
implements java.lang.CharSequence, java.lang.Appendable
    A class that represents String type data field.
    It can hold String of arbitrary length, however due to use of short value as length specifier when serializing/ deserializing value to/from ByteBuffer, the maximum length is limited to 32762 characters (Short.MAX_VALUE);
    Since:
    March 27, 2002
    See Also:
    DataFieldMetadata, Serialized Form

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Description copied from class: DataField
        An operation which sets/resets field to its initial value (just after it was created by JVM) - it varies depending on type of field.
        Nullable fields are set to NULL, non-nullable are zeroed, if they have default value defined, then default value is assigned.
        Specified by:
        reset in class DataField

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Description copied from class: DataField
        Checks whether two DataField objects are equal. Both fiels should be of the same type. If they are not, ClassCastException is thrown.
